In this article, several governors express their support for President Obama's fiscal policy speech. Minnesota Governor Mark Dayton commends the President for his balanced approach to reducing the national deficit, which includes asking the wealthiest Americans to contribute more. Maryland Governor Martin O'Malley criticizes the Republicans' budget proposals, stating that they would burden the middle class and jeopardize the economy. Delaware Governor Jack Markell applauds the President for addressing the issue of federal deficits and debt, and expresses his commitment to tackling this challenge. Vermont Governor Peter Shumlin supports the President's emphasis on shared responsibility and a balanced approach to revenues and spending. Connecticut Governor Dannel P. Malloy commends President Obama for taking a measured and responsible approach to the issue of fiscal sustainability. Massachusetts Governor Deval Patrick thanks the President for his leadership and vision, stating that it aligns with the kind of country most Americans want to live in.